    "revise": "You are the FIGURE REVISER (Opus) for \"The LLM Stack\". Chapter: content/07-inference-serving/06-speculative-decoding.md\nThe chapter's core intuitions: Decode is memory-bandwidth bound: a target forward pass over K tokens costs about the same wall-clock time as over 1 token, because weight movement (loading all parameters from HBM) dominates and per-token math is nearly free. This is the whole reason verification-of-many can be as cheap as decode-of-one.; Draft-then-verify: a cheap drafter proposes gamma tokens autoregressively; the expensive target verifies all gamma+1 positions in ONE parallel pass; a step emits an accepted prefix plus one corrected-or-bonus token, advancing 1..gamma+1 positions per target pass.; The accept/reject rule is EXACT: accept a drafted x~q with prob min(1,p/q), else resample from the residual (p-q)_+ and stop. The emitted mass decomposes as min(p,q) + (p-q)_+ = p for ANY drafter, so correctness is free; the drafter only affects speed via alpha = sum min(p,q) = 1 - TV(p,q).; Drafter families trade acceptance alpha against draft cost c: a smaller same-family/distilled model, Medusa parallel heads (each predicts a future token in isolation from one hidden state), EAGLE feature-space autoregression (conditions on drafted tokens for much higher alpha), and near-free n-gram/prompt-lookup drafting.\n\nReview each of these figures (the ones this chapter just drew/edited):\n  spec-decoding\n\nFor EACH: render and SEE it \u2014 `python3 scripts/preview_fig.py <NAME> --theme both` from /local-ssd/pk669/programming/llm-stack-textbook,\nthen view /tmp/figpreview/<NAME>.light.png and .dark.png. Judge strictly:\n  - Does it actually BUILD INTUITION for its concept (not just decorate)? Is it correct vs the chapter?\n  - Theme-safe (no hardcoded primary color; readable in BOTH light and dark)?\n  - Nothing clipped by the viewBox; no illegible overlaps; no tofu glyphs (ASCII only in the SVG)?\n  - Marker present in the chapter exactly once; figcaption has a bold lead + takeaway?\nIf a figure has ANY problem, FIX it: Edit /local-ssd/pk669/programming/llm-stack-textbook/figures/<NAME>.html (and re-render to confirm), or\nfix a missing/duplicate marker in the chapter. Re-verify after fixing.\n\nSet verdict per figure: good / fixed / still-broken / missing. `passed` = every figure good-or-fixed\nAND present. Return the structured object."
